// VortXEdge.xcconfig.example  --  COMMITTED TEMPLATE (no real secret here).
//
// Copy this to `VortXEdge.xcconfig` (same directory) and fill in the real value to enable
// client-side request signing against the hardened VortX edge workers:
//
//     cp app/Config/VortXEdge.xcconfig.example app/Config/VortXEdge.xcconfig
//
// `VortXEdge.xcconfig` is GITIGNORED and MUST NEVER be committed. The VortX repo is public; a
// secret in git history is leaked forever. Keep the real value only in the local gitignored file
// and in CI (a GitHub Actions repo secret), never in the tracked tree.
//
// VORTX_EDGE_SECRET holds the MASKED secret blob, NOT the raw hex key. It is exactly the string returned
// by VortXEdgeAuth.maskedValue(for: "<64-hex>"): the 64-char hex secret XORed with the runtime mask and
// base64-encoded. At build time it substitutes $(VORTX_EDGE_SECRET) into Info.plist (key `VortXEdgeSecret`);
// at runtime SourcesShared/VortXEdgeAuth.swift de-masks it back to the hex secret and signs requests to OUR
// gated edge hosts (skip / trickplay / ratings / poster / erdb / trailer .vortx.tv) with X-VX-Ts + X-VX-Sig.
//
// DO NOT paste the raw 64-char hex key here. The de-mask path (VortXEdgeAuth.swift:72-82) XORs whatever it
// finds against the mask, so a raw-hex value de-masks to non-hex bytes, fails the 64-hex validity check, and
// SILENTLY collapses the secret to empty: no build error, no runtime warning, signing just turns into a
// no-op, and the day enforce is flipped on every such build is locked out with no visible cause. Always run
// the value through maskedValue(for:) first.
//
// EMPTY is safe: the workers run in OBSERVE mode, so an absent/empty secret produces a no-op /
// empty-key signature that observe lets through. Leave it blank for local builds; the owner
// provisions the real value before enforce is flipped on.
VORTX_EDGE_SECRET =
